{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}
'''Sir John Campbell''' (c. 1576{{spaced ndash}}c. 1642) was a Scottish nobleman and knight, who was the son of Archibald Campbell, and Isabella Grant, a daughter of James Grant, laird of Freuchie and Elizabeth Forbes.
[[Angus MacDonald, 8th of Dunnyveg]] sold the lands belonging to the [[Clan MacDonald of Dunnyveg|MacDonald's]] on [[Islay]] to Sir John Campbell of Cawdor for 6,000 [[Merk (coin)|merks]] in 1612. Several young chiefs of Clan MacDonald occupied [[Dunyvaig Castle]] and [[Loch Gorm Castle]] in defiance of Cawdor. Dunyvaig Castle was retaken by Cawdor and Loch Gorm Castle surrendered on 28 January 1615. He purchased the lands on [[Islay]] and [[Jura, Scotland|Jura]] which had previously belonged to the [[Clan Maclean|Macleans of Duart]] in 1615.
==Family== By his wife, Jean, daughter of Sir Duncan Campbell, Baronet and Jean Stewart, their children were: *John Campbell *Jane Campbell *Colin Campbell *Robert Campbell *George Campbell *Duncan Campbell *Alexander Campbell *Jean Campbell
