{{Infobox television | show_name = Prehistoric Megastorms | image = | caption = | executive_producer = | country = {{USA}} | network = [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History Channel]] | first_aired = 2008 |picture_format = | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = 7 }}
'''''Prehistoric Megastorms''''' is a [[paleontology]]-based American [[documentary film|documentary]] [[television series]] that premiered in 2008 on the [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History Channel]]. The episodes concern a [[Comet storm]], the [[Great Flood of Noah]], the [[Megaflood|British Superflood]], [[Dinosaur extinction|Asteroid Apocalypse]], [[Hypercane]], a [[Mega Tsunami]], and [[Volcanic winter]].
==Episodes==
===1 Hypercane=== 65 million years ago the asteroid of the [[Yucatan Peninsula]] could have caused a giant storm that might have killed 70 percent of all animals on earth.
===2 Noah's Great Flood=== 8000 years ago the [[Ice Age]] ended. Then a [[outburst flood|superflood]] bursts in a lush forest known now as the [[Black Sea]].
===3 Mega Tsunami=== A giant wall of water strikes the [[mediterranean sea]] [[6000 BC]] destroying civllatiations built by our forfathers. Could it have destroyed the mediterraean? And could it happen again?
==See also== * ''[[Animal Armageddon]]'' * ''[[Jurassic Fight Club]]'' * ''[[Mega Disasters]]''
